&gt; Hi,
&gt; I was wondering if anyone could help me out setting up junit to test
&gt; EJBs. I downloaded a copy of junit from an article on www.javaworld.com
&gt; by Michael Nygard and Traci Karsjens entitled &quot;Test infect your
&gt; Enterprise Java Beans&quot;. I&#39;ve tried going through the procedure for
&gt; getting the test example working, but to no avail - the code compiles,
&gt; packages and deploys fine, but when I enter the test suite class file
&gt; name in the first servlet form and then hit enter, I get an internal
&gt; server error, with a
&gt; NoClassDefFoundError being thrown for class junit.framework.TestCase.
&gt; Following the stack trace indicates that it gets thrown by the servlet
&gt; when it&#39;s trying to load the test suite class: -
&gt; 
&gt; package junit.servletui;
&gt; ....
&gt; public class TestRunner extends HttpServlet {
&gt; ....
&gt;   protected Test createTestSuite(...) {
&gt;     ...
&gt;     try {
&gt;       testClass = Class.forName(classUnderTest); // Error here.
&gt;     }...}...}
&gt; 
&gt; Class.forName can find classUnderTest, but not TestCase, which it
&gt; extends.
&gt; 
&gt; The web application all seems to be packaged fine -
&gt; junit.framework.TestCase is present in the .WAR file in WEB-INF/classes,
&gt; the servlet engine just doesn&#39;t seem to be able to see it. 
&gt; 
&gt; I realise that this is possibly more of a question about web application
&gt; deployment than junit itself, but any pointers would be appreciated.
